{"timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:42:39.669Z","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","session_id":"bf6aaf6c-1e94-49db-9cdd-23a32a284525","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/bf6aaf6c-1e94-49db-9cdd-23a32a284525.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: Dashboard Responsive Layout\n\n## Goal\nMake `/dashboard` fill the full screen width and work well on mobile phones using a card layout.\n\n## Decisions\n- Wide screen: table takes nearly full width; long URL column fills remaining space\n- Mobile (< md breakpoint): swap table for collapsible cards\n- Card default state: shortcode + status + truncated URL (one line)\n- Card expanded state: shortcode + status + full break-all URL as link + Created + Expires dates\n- Only one card can be expanded at a time (accordion style), indicated by ChevronDown/ChevronUp icon\n- Breakpoint: `md` (768px) separates table view from card view\n\n## Only modified file\n`frontend/src/views/DashboardView.vue`\n\n## All changes\n\n### 1. Script section additions\n- Import `ref` (already imported), add `ChevronDown`, `ChevronUp` from `lucide-vue-next`\n- Add `const expandedId = ref<string | null>(null)`\n- Add `function toggleCard(id: string) { expandedId.value = expandedId.value === id ? null : id }`\n\n### 2. Outer container padding\n- `p-8` → `p-4 sm:p-8`\n\n### 3. Long URL TableCell class\n- Remove `max-w-xs`, keep `truncate text-muted-foreground` (column naturally fills remaining width via table layout)\n\n### 4. Restructure the v-else block into `<template v-else>`\nWrap the existing table div and the new card section together:\n```\n<template v-else>\n  <!-- Table: md+ only -->\n  <div class=\"hidden md:block rounded-md border\">\n    ... (existing table, unchanged except Long URL cell class) ...\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Cards: < md only -->\n  <div class=\"md:hidden flex flex-col gap-3\">\n    <!-- empty state -->\n    <p v-if=\"urlsStore.items.length === 0\" class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground py-8 text-center\">\n      You haven't created any short URLs yet.\n    </p>\n    <!-- card per URL -->\n    <div\n      v-for=\"url in urlsStore.items\"\n      :key=\"url.id\"\n      class=\"rounded-md border p-4 flex flex-col gap-2 cursor-pointer\"\n      @click=\"toggleCard(url.id)\"\n    >\n      <!-- row 1: shortcode + badge + chevron -->\n      <div class=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n        <span class=\"font-mono font-medium flex-1\">{{ url.shortcode }}</span>\n        <Badge v-if=\"isExpired(url.expires_at)\" variant=\"destructive\">Expired</Badge>\n        <Badge v-else variant=\"secondary\">Active</Badge>\n        <ChevronDown v-if=\"expandedId !== url.id\" class=\"h-4 w-4 text-muted-foreground\" />\n        <ChevronUp v-else class=\"h-4 w-4 text-muted-foreground\" />\n      </div>\n      <!-- row 2: truncated URL (always visible) -->\n      <span class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground truncate\">{{ url.long_url }}</span>\n      <!-- expanded details -->\n      <template v-if=\"expandedId === url.id\">\n        <a\n          :href=\"url.long_url\"\n          target=\"_blank\"\n          rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\n          class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground break-all hover:underline\"\n          @click.stop\n        >\n          {{ url.long_url }}\n        </a>\n        <div class=\"flex gap-4 text-xs text-muted-foreground\">\n          <span>Created {{ formatDate(url.created_at) }}</span>\n          <span v-if=\"url.expires_at\">Expires {{ formatDate(url.expires_at) }}</span>\n          <span v-else>No expiry</span>\n        </div>\n      </template>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\nNote: `@click.stop` on the link prevents the card toggle from firing when tapping the URL link.\n\n## Verification\n1. On desktop (>= 768px): table visible, cards hidden. Long URL column fills remaining width and truncates if too long.\n2. On mobile (< 768px): table hidden, cards visible. Each card shows shortcode + status + truncated URL. Tap expands to show full URL link and dates.\n3. On very wide screen (1920px+): long URL may display fully without truncation.\n4. No changes to store, router, or any other file.\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DffRoeFpbvngs8HPxwWKf3__vscode-1773497712790","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

